<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-08-12T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-08-12T17:00:00-05:00" n="1013" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1013">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">622.116/119a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Long</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-08-12T18:00:00-04:00">August 12, 1940—6
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>110. The Department has been informed that the Ecuadoran Consul in New
                            York has been instructed to require exporters to present, beginning
                            today, Ecuadoran import licenses as a requisite for certification of
                            documents.</p>
                        <p>Please investigate and report by telegraph.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>